body:
@csantanapr Thank you, Carlos.

@rabbah This issue is where to break the circular dependency, and we propose to remove the catalog(packages) installation in openwhisk. Instead, where are we going to install and test the catalog(packages)? Go to openwhisk-catalog. This is destination, where we can move all the catalog((packages) and the tests into.

As @csantanapr described in the previous comment. Both openwhisk and openwhisk-catalog need some changes to make this happen, including catalog folder, tests of catalog(packages), travis ci for openwhisk-catalog, etc.

@lfzCarlosC 
I use "ant build" to build all projects.
The test command should be "gradle test". You can try.

@csantanapr I think we need a developer guide.

@daisy-ycguo  
Could you tell me from which directory do you use to execute this? openwhisk home dir? and you execute command "vagrant ssh -- ant build" or "ant build" on host machine? I execute ant build on home directory and it thorws error:
     [taskdef] Could not load definitions from resource net/sf/antcontrib/antlib.xml. It could not be found.

These two are defined in the property playbook:

whisk.version.name={{ whisk_version_name }}
whisk.version.date={{ whisk.version.date }}
